*** INTRODUCTION ***

RudeServer is a CGI application that uses the RudeWebPlatform architecture
and an XSLT processor to generate dynamic web content.

The main responsibilities of the RudeServer program are:

	1. Configure global (singleton) Database objects
	2. Configure the global Session object
	3. Build and Execute requested commands
	4. Build the requested decorated views
	4. Determine the appropriate output device (html, wml, etc...)
	5. Build the xsl template based on the required device
	6. Perform XSLT Translation on the XMl output of the view(s)
	7. Determine the appropriate output language
	8. Perform Worldet substitution
	9. Clean-up global objects

Documentation, discussions, and new releases are available at 

http://www.rudeserver.com/

See file `COPYING' for copying conditions.
See file `INSTALL' for compilation and installation instructions.
See file `NEWS' for a list of major changes in the current release.
See file `THANKS' for a list of contributors.
See file 'AUTHORS' for contact information


*** BUG REPORTING ***

Please Send bug reports to <bug-rudeserver@rudeserver.com>.
A bug report should contain an adequate description of the 
problem, your input, what you expected, what you got, 
and why this is wrong.  Where applicable, please submit actual data
files with your report. 

Your feedback will help us to make a better and more portable package.
Consider documentation errors as bugs, and report them as such.  If you
develop anything pertaining to RudeServer or have suggestions, let us know
and share your findings by writing to <bug-rudeserver@rudeserver.com> or
by visiting the discussion forum accessable from the RudeServer 
website at http://www.rudeserver.com/



